# IPL 2026 Playoff Race: Where Every Team Stands

The IPL 2026 playoff race has entered its most dramatic stage with multiple franchises still battling for a place in the top four.

Gujarat Titans and Royal Challengers Bengaluru have placed themselves in strong positions near the top of the table, while several teams remain locked in a tight contest for the remaining qualification spots. Net Run Rate has also become a major factor as margins between teams continue to shrink.

Punjab Kings, Chennai Super Kings, and Rajasthan Royals are among the sides still fighting to keep their playoff hopes alive heading into the final round of league matches. Every victory now carries enormous importance as qualification scenarios continue changing after almost every game.

The battle for the top two positions is equally significant because of the advantage offered during the IPL playoff structure. Teams finishing in the top two receive an extra opportunity to reach the final through Qualifier 1.

Fans across the cricket world are closely monitoring the standings as IPL 2026 moves closer to the knockout rounds and the race for the trophy intensifies.

